00:00:02.280 --> 00:00:10.559
&gt;&gt;Female Presenter: My name is Lauren Hannah-Murphy
and I'm really excited that we have our first

00:00:10.559 --> 00:00:11.559
Filmmakers@Google event today.

00:00:11.559 --> 00:00:16.160
And I'm really excited to introduce Doug Hannah,
who is my younger brother.

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:21.900
So I think it's safe to say I have known him
his whole life.

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:22.900
[laughter]

00:00:22.900 --> 00:00:27.860
And from the moment that my Dad got his first
camcorder, he was making movies of one sort

00:00:27.860 --> 00:00:28.860
or another.

00:00:28.860 --> 00:00:31.890
Sometimes he was in front of the camera.

00:00:31.890 --> 00:00:33.540
Sometimes, he was behind.

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:38.429
So, it's always been pretty obvious that he
was going to do something with film.

00:00:38.429 --> 00:00:45.370
There was a short period of time when he had
me taping him as he would climb out from our

00:00:45.370 --> 00:00:49.510
second floor and climb down the tree 'cause
he thought he wanted to be a stunt man.

00:00:49.510 --> 00:00:52.390
But that didn't last too long.

00:00:52.390 --> 00:00:53.390
[laughter]

00:00:53.390 --> 00:01:00.579
And he went to school for Film and now has
been doing a lot of editing and film-making.

00:01:00.579 --> 00:01:04.059
So, he's here today--without any of our home
videos, thankfully--but has his short film,

00:01:04.059 --> 00:01:08.750
"Good News, Oklahoma!" and I'll let him introduce
that.

00:01:08.750 --> 00:01:14.880
So, please join me in welcoming Doug Hannah.

00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:15.880
[applause]

00:01:15.880 --> 00:01:19.479
&gt;&gt;Doug Hannah: Thank you, guys.

00:01:19.479 --> 00:01:23.690
That was a very good introduction.

00:01:23.690 --> 00:01:26.820
Way more personal than any of the other introductions
I've had so far.

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:27.820
[laughter]

00:01:27.820 --> 00:01:30.950
Well, thank you guys all for coming and watching
my short film.

00:01:30.950 --> 00:01:35.240
We made this last year at the end of December.

00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:37.200
So, this has been around for about a year.

00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:38.799
We've been doing the festival circuits.

00:01:38.799 --> 00:01:42.780
I think we've screened it at about nine film
festivals so far.

00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:47.000
It won Best Comedy Short at the Atlanta Short
Fest, which was our first festival.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.549
So right off the bat, it was really pretty
exciting.

00:01:51.549 --> 00:01:56.009
I work for White Collar, which is a USA TV
show.

00:01:56.009 --> 00:01:59.439
And the writer is also a writer for White
Collar.

00:01:59.439 --> 00:02:04.149
And about at the end of Season Two, we were
talking about what we were gonna do during

00:02:04.149 --> 00:02:05.149
our break.

00:02:05.149 --> 00:02:10.910
And I was wanting to direct a short, 'cause
I'm trying to finagle my way out of editing,

00:02:10.910 --> 00:02:16.140
since I'm getting sick of sitting in a dark
room all the time and getting into more of

00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:18.099
the directing side of things.

00:02:18.099 --> 00:02:21.670
And she had a few shorts and she pitched me
a couple ideas.

00:02:21.670 --> 00:02:25.370
And she talked about this idea called "Good
News, Oklahoma!"

00:02:25.370 --> 00:02:29.750
And instantly, I really knew I wanted to make
it.

00:02:29.750 --> 00:02:33.280
I won't go too much into the plot now, since
we're about to watch it.

00:02:33.280 --> 00:02:38.940
But I'm pretty addicted to news and watch
a lot of news and stuff.

00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:41.560
And so, this was one of the reasons why I
wanted to make it.

00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:45.840
And I'll go more into the other reasons why
I wanted to make it after you see it.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:52.260
But yeah, I think I'll leave it at that.

00:02:52.260 --> 00:02:55.549
Channing Powell is who wrote it--a really
talented writer.

00:02:55.549 --> 00:02:59.799
And it was really fun getting to work with
her.

00:02:59.799 --> 00:03:03.000
And if you're watching this online, it's just
gonna be a trailer.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:08.760
I can't put the whole movie online 'cause
a lot of film festivals will only accept movies

00:03:08.760 --> 00:03:10.510
that are not screened online.

00:03:10.510 --> 00:03:15.370
They want it to have some type of premier
status more than anyone just being able to

00:03:15.370 --> 00:03:16.370
watch it.

00:03:16.370 --> 00:03:18.629
But all you guys can watch it now.

00:03:18.629 --> 00:03:23.549
And then from here, we're going out to Denver
next weekend for the Festivus Film Festival.

00:03:23.549 --> 00:03:26.330
So, we're excited about that.

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:27.330
But yeah.

00:03:27.330 --> 00:03:29.140
Without further ado, here's a short film.

00:03:29.140 --> 00:03:30.140
It's 18 minutes.

00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:31.140
17:56.

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:32.140
[laughter]

00:03:32.140 --> 00:03:33.140
It's called "Good News, Oklahoma!"

00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:34.140
[plays film]

